HEADWORD: Hydropneumatic
<hw>Hy`dro*pneu*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 1 + <ets>pneumatic</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>hydropneumatique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to, or depending
upon, both liquid and gaseous substances; <as>as,
<ex>hydropneumatic</ex> apparatus for collecting gases over water or
other liquids</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydropneumatic gun carriage</ent>⟦br⟧
